      "suggested_payload_hint": "GET /api/dev/mail with no cookies; poll repeatedly to harvest password-reset and invite tokens addressed to other users."
    },
    {
      "path": "<api:/api/dev/mail>",
      "cap": "CSRF",
      "endpoint": "DELETE /api/dev/mail (unauthenticated, no CSRF token)",
      "rationale": "DELETE /api/dev/mail wipes captured-mail spool with no auth and no CSRF token (verified: 200 OK {\"ok\":true} with no cookies and with cross-origin Origin: https://evil.com). Other mutating routes such as POST /api/me are gated by 'Missing CSRF token' (403), so the omission on /api/dev/mail is an inconsistent state-machine gap. Browsers will normally block cross-origin DELETE via preflight (server returns no Access-Control-Allow-Origin) but any attacker with network access or same-origin XSS can erase forensic evidence.",
      "suggested_payload_hint": "curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8787/api/dev/mail (no Cookie, no X-CSRF-Token)"
    },
    {
